    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1922-04-21T13:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1922-04-21T13:00:00-05:00" n="211"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d211">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">723.2515/906: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Chargé in Peru</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Sterling</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Paraphrase]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Lima</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1922-04-21T13:00:00-05:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">April 21, 1922—1 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                        <lb/>[Received 11:50 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>36. Your no. 36, April 19, 6 p.m. The Grace steamer <hi rend="italic">Santa
                        Teresa</hi> leaves here the 26th instant with Ambassador Pezet on board due
                    to arrive May 8 in New York. He carries the Government’s instructions to the
                    Peruvian delegates which would have been given to Velarde had he come to Lima as
                    planned. Inasmuch as until Pezet arrives, the delegates will be without either
                    instructions or credentials, it is of no advantage that Porras sail before the
                    26th; I did not, therefore, urge his earlier departure. The Minister of Foreign
                    Affairs, however, has given me positive assurance that Porras will not again
                    postpone sailing, and that the delegates will be assembled and prepared for the
                    conference at a date not later than May 15. If this date can be definitely
                    fixed, the Minister would be glad to be so informed immediately.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Sterling</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
